Class CCPersonBuilderBase<T extends Person,B extends CCPersonBuilderBase<T,B>>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PersonBuilder

    public class CCPersonBuilderBase<T extends Person,B extends CCPersonBuilderBase<T,B>>
extends PersonBuilderBase<T,B>
    CC specific base class for Person builders. If you are creating a builder for a specific subclass of person you should usually extend this class rather than PersonBuilder because it allows you to add type specific methods that can be chained together

      • withPrimaryAddressSetEarly

        public B withPrimaryAddressSetEarly(Address address)
        Sets the primary address on the company and also sets the initialization order of the address so it will be set up before other fields on the company. This is useful because the country of the primary address is used to determine the validators for other fields on the contact (such as phone number and tax identification number) so the primary address should typically be one of the first fields to be set.
        Parameters:
        address - the desired primary address
        Returns:
        the modified builder
